Ally Financial Inc. (NYSE:ALLY) Stock Traded 6.1% Above Its 50 Day Moving Average - Highlight Press

























































Highlight PressBreaking Tech News, Entertainment, Mortgages and More
Ally Financial Inc. (NYSE:ALLY) Stock Traded 6.1% Above Its 50 Day Moving Average
July 25, 2017 By Clarence Martin Tweet        Advertisement





Shares of the company are trading at $21.87 marginally over the 50 day moving average of $20.61 and which is marginally higher than the 200 day moving average of $20.54.  The 50 day moving average moved up $1.26 and the 200 day average went up by +6.50%.  371K shares changed hands on Tuesday.  Volume was down 88.13% under the stocks average daily volume. 
 The following firms have also recently changed their position in ALLY.   Financial Architects, Inc added to its investment by buying 179 shares an increase of 13.8% from 03/31/2017 to 06/30/2017. Financial Architects, Inc controls 1,478 shares worth $31,000. The total value of its holdings increased 19.2%. State Treasurer State Of Michigan bolstered its position by buying 200,000 shares an increase of 16.2% as of 06/30/2017. State Treasurer State Of Michigan currently owns 1,430,966 shares valued at $29,907,000. The value of the position overall is up by 19.5%.
 As of quarter end Aperio Group, LLC had acquired 41,179 shares growing its holdings by 25.6%. The value of the total investment in Ally Financial Inc. increased from $3,269,000 to $4,221,000 a change of $952,000 quarter to quarter. As of the end of the quarter Nisa Investment Advisors, LLC had bought  a total of 23,375 shares growing its position 86.3%. The value of the company’s investment in Ally Financial Inc. went from $551,000 to $1,012,000 a change of 83.7% quarter over quarter.
  On July 17 the company was rated “Underweight” in a report from Stephens & Co. which is down from the previous “Equal-Weight” rating. On June 9 analysts at PiperJaffray added ALLY to its research portfolio by announcing an initial rating of “Overweight”.





 On November 1, 2016 Stephens & Co. starting coverage on the stock with an initial rating of “Equal-Weight”. Equity analyst Macquarie began coverage of ALLY giving it an initial rating of “Neutral”.
 On April 27, 2016 the stock rating was set at “Market Perform” according to a Wells Fargo report down from the previous “Outperform” rating. On April 8 the company was downgraded from “Buy” to “Neutral” by Bank of America.
 In the market the company is trading down by -0.27 percent from yesterday’s close.  Additionally Ally Financial Inc. announced a dividend payable on Tuesday the 15th of August 2017.  The dividend payment will be $0.120 per share for the quarter which comes to $0.48 on an annualized basis.  The dividend yield will be $2.19.  The ex-dividend date is Thursday the 27th of April 2017. 
 The P/E ratio is 10.28 and market capitalization is 10.49B.  In the last earnings report the EPS was $2.13 and is estimated to be $2.23 for the current year with 479,800,000 shares now outstanding.  Next quarter’s EPS is forecasted at $0.61 with next year’s EPS projected to be $2.63. 
 Ally Financial Inc., launched on February 21, 1997, is a digital financial services company. The Company is a bank and financial holding company. The Company offers various financial products for consumers, businesses, automotive dealers and corporate clients. The Business’s segments include Automotive Finance operations, Insurance operations, Mortgage Finance operations, Corporate Finance operations, and Corporate and Other. Dealer Financial Services business line includes the Business’s Automotive Finance and Insurance segments. Its primary customers are automotive dealers, which are typically independently owned businesses. Its Dealer Financial Services operations offer a range of financial services and insurance products to automotive..






